PROJECT AXIOM: MASTER STRATEGIC PLAN

1. Identity & Vision

Project Name: Project AXIOM (The Axiom Engine)
Type: Deterministic Content Execution System (SaaS Infrastructure)
Core Philosophy: "Writer executes. Analytics observes. KB learns."
Deployment Target: Production-Grade Enterprise Environment (Not MVP).

Critical Directive:
We are NOT building a generic AI wrapper. We are building a self-healing marketing infrastructure. The system must be deterministic, strictly typed, and fault-tolerant. "Hallucinations" or "Best Guesses" are system failures.

2. The Technology Stack (Non-Negotiable)

Infrastructure (Monorepo)

Orchestration: Docker Compose (Service-based architecture).

Containerization: Multi-stage Dockerfiles for optimized production builds.

The Brain (Backend)

Runtime: Node.js (v20+ LTS).

Language: TypeScript (Strict Mode).

Framework: Express.js (Modular Router Pattern).

Validation: Zod (The absolute law. All inputs/outputs must be validated against Zod schemas matching the Client Contracts).

Scheduling: node-cron (For the 06:00 AM Ops Loop).

The Face (Frontend)

Framework: Next.js 14+ (App Router).

Language: TypeScript.

Styling: Tailwind CSS (Enterprise UI Kit).

State: React Server Components (RSC) where possible.

The Memory (Database)

Database: PostgreSQL 16+.

Driver: node-postgres (pg).

Strategy: JSONB Heavy.

Why: The client's schemas (KB, Input, Output) are complex and nested. We store them as validated JSONB documents to allow schema evolution without painful SQL migrations.

3. The Architecture (Service Map)

The project follows a strict Separation of Concerns:

graph TD
    User[Admin User] -->|HTTPS| Web[Next.js Frontend]
    Web -->|REST API| API[Node.js Backend]
    
    subgraph "The Axiom Engine (Backend)"
        API --> Validator[Zod Schema Guard]
        Validator --> Engine[Writer Engine]
        Validator --> Loop[Learning Loop]
        
        Engine -->|Reads| DB[(Postgres DB)]
        Loop -->|Updates| DB
        
        Cron[Ops Scheduler] -->|Triggers 6AM| Loop
    end


4. Execution Standards

No "Any" Types: TypeScript strict: true is mandatory.

Schema First: Do not write logic until the Zod schema is defined.

Error Handling: Global Error Handlers in Express. No silent failures.

Logging: Structured logging (JSON format) for all system events.

